one_reviews_text: Actually, if you crush up and turn fireflies into juice, you can drink it, and fix your bones and regrow teeth, etc

Developer's note:  This application is in early stages.  Much value is added by taking time to review range of motion session data  through the web portal.  Would encourage any users to experience this in VR, but then goto the personalized web portal to see a visualization of motion.
Interesting health care related app that assesses your shoulder/arm movement for limitations and then provides games to help address your issues.

Very lightweight app that won't show your results in app. You have to go onto a website and give them your email. Seems like it's phishing

Updated: The developer contacted me (below) to let me know the issues I have are due to early access and they don't have in-app results yet.  Still, it would be good to alert people upfront that they won't be able to get any info before they go through the experience. Right now you don't know that's going to be the case and go through the evaluation, just to not be able to get your results at the end. Some more transparency at the start would go a long way here.

If email is required, ask for it upfront.
review_feedback: Reach Shoulder Health is currently in Early Access and serves as a tool for you to capture a volumetric profile of your current shoulder movement abilities. We provide detailed reporting on your shoulder health that is best accessed in a web browser rather than VR, and that is why we ask for your email. We take our users privacy seriously and creating a Reach account with us is completely optional and not necessary if you do not want to view your reports. Thank you for your comment though, as it helps us understand what could potentially be in the minds of other people as well

one_reviews_text: This is a neat tool to be able to analyze my shoulder health. The web portal is a neat, additional experience that helps me go more in depth with seeing my progress.
It was interesting to be able to view each of my arms capacities for movement. Excited to see what comes next.
